Welcome To MY WORLD

ABOUT ME

A "witch in the age of entanglement

Being intrigued by how creativity and technology are integrated into the works of Katie Paterson, whose works combine a Romantic sensibility with a research-based approach, conceptual rigour and coolly minimalist presentation, I realize that 2D design is far from enough: I have to use 3D or even 4D technologies to reconstruct something and address the complex challenges facing the world.


While exploring speculative design and ranking top among my class in graphic design, I have also been interning at a laboratory in the College of Computer Science and Technology, where I have been conducting interdisciplinary research for nearly two years.


I want to become a designer who speaks out for equality and justice and creates value for society, instead of merely exhibiting my criticism of the external world. With my keen interest in traditional culture, I would like to break down the barriers to secondary innovation of traditional crafts. I am eager to work towards an “anti-disciplinary” future. In my dream, my project would appear in the Museum of Modern Art and on the covers of Nature and Science.
